      "mode": "explore",
      "title": "8-bit Adder",
      "instructions": "# 8-bit Adder\n\nEvery CPU needs arithmetic. Build an 8-bit adder with carry-in and carry-out.\n\n## Goal\n\nConnect two 8-bit inputs **A** and **B** and a 1-bit **Cin** through an `Add` component to produce an 8-bit sum **S** and a 1-bit carry-out **Cout**.\n\n## Hints\n\n- Use the `Add` component with `bitWidth = 8`\n- The carry-in allows chaining adders for wider arithmetic\n- Verify: 1 + 1 = 2, and 255 + 1 = 0 with carry",
