      "mode": "explore",
      "title": "8-bit ALU",
      "instructions": "# 8-bit ALU\n\nAn ALU performs different operations based on an opcode. Build one that supports ADD, SUB, AND, and OR.\n\n## Goal\n\nRoute two 8-bit inputs **A** and **B** through four parallel operations (Add, Sub, And, Or), then use a 4-input multiplexer selected by a 2-bit **Op** to choose the result.\n\n## Operation Table\n\n| Op | Operation |\n|----|-----------|\n| 0  | A + B     |\n| 1  | A - B     |\n| 2  | A AND B   |\n| 3  | A OR B    |\n\n## Hints\n\n- All four operations compute in parallel- the mux just selects which result to output\n- Tie the carry-in pins on Add and Sub to a `Const(0)` to ground them\n- The carry-out from the Add is useful for the flags register later",
